
🛠 Beginner Scalping Indicator Setup

Chart Timeframes

1-Minute (1M) → ultra-short scalping

5-Minute (5M) → slightly slower trades, good for beginners



---

1️⃣ Trend Indicator: EMA Crossover

EMA 9 (fast) → tracks very short-term price changes

EMA 21 (slow) → confirms trend direction

Signal:

EMA 9 crosses above EMA 21 → potential buy

EMA 9 crosses below EMA 21 → potential sell




---

2️⃣ Momentum Indicator: RSI (14)

Settings: 14-period

Signal:

RSI 40–70 → trending market, safe entry

RSI > 70 → overbought → avoid buying

RSI < 30 → oversold → avoid selling




---

3️⃣ Confirmation Indicator: Volume

Add Volume Bars

Signal: Enter trade only if volume is higher than the last 2–3 candles

Confirms that price movement is supported by strong trading activity



---

✅ Optional Extra (for more confirmation)

MACD (12,26,9) → helps confirm trend strength

Bollinger Bands (20,2) → identifies overbought/oversold in volatile markets



---

💡 How to Use This Setup (Step-by-Step)

1. Check the trend → EMA 9/21 crossover


2. Confirm momentum → RSI in safe zone (40–70 for long trades)


3. Check volume → enter only if volume is rising


4. Set stop-loss → just below recent candle low (for longs) or high (for shorts)


5. Set take-profit → start with 0.5–1% on 1M charts, 1–3% on 5M charts




---

Best Pairs to Use This Setup

Bitcoin / Tether (BTC/USDT)

Ethereum / Tether (ETH/USDT)

Solana / Tether (SOL/USDT)


---

⚠️ Important Beginner Tips

Start small: $50–$200 per trade

Never chase pumps → wait for EMA + RSI + Volume alignment

Avoid trading low-liquidity coins on 1M charts → spreads are too wide


